			<ns0:name>bradc...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/110304265766688778552/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;
With Pepper2 there is no sensible way for an app to access the contents of a file named by a URL as a read-only file.

&lt;b&gt;- Why is this a problem?&lt;/b&gt;
This is an important use case for graphics assets etc.

&lt;b&gt;- The proposed enhancement:&lt;/b&gt;
Add ability to fetch a URL's contents via a file descriptor, read-only. Similar to capability required to fetch nexes

&lt;b&gt;- Exit criteria:&lt;/b&gt;
Read-only file access is easy to implement and provides reasonable performance.

&lt;b&gt;- Anticipated impact:&lt;/b&gt;
Applications get useful access to URL contents as read-only file.
